Manchester United squad on Friday crowned goalkeeper David De Gea as the Player of the Year for 2021/22. De Gea won the award ahead of Cristiano Ronaldo and Fred. The Spaniard performed consistently and produced many sublime saves for Man United during the just concluded 2022/21 season. The 31-year-old played every single minute of Premier League action and was regularly on hand to save his side. He accumulated a total of seven Man-of-the-Match awards during the campaign, with only Ronaldo having claimed as many. The Spaniard also earned the Player of the Month award for November, December and January.